==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Discoloration
<hw>Dis*col`or*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>decoloration</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of discoloring,
or the state of being discolored; alteration of hue or appearance.</def>
<rj><au>Darwin.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A discolored spot; a stain.</def>
<rj><au>Arbuthnot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>discolored</ent>⟦br⟧
